<h2>Anutan</h2>
<p>Anuta is a tiny volcanic island which, though located within the Solomon Islands of Melanesia, 
is populated by Polynesians. Stars provide the Anutans' most important tool for long range 
navigation. Major guiding stars and constellations are known as 'kaavenga'. Star paths that are 
followed from one island to the next (even if they have not risen, or already set) are called 
'kau panogna porau'. Unnamed stars which are not used as major navigational aids are called 
'petuu vare' (foolish, common, or undistinguished).</p>

